    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see what you mean about essentialism. but some researchers suggest that even if you control for income and education, there's still a delta that's hard to explain just with policing or poverty. if you were looking at this from a strictly data-driven, non-political perspective, would you say that some groups' behavioral trends or community norms are actually contributing to the stats, or is it always just a byproduct of the system?",
